.TH "vmw_dma_select_mode" 9 "vmw_dma_select_mode" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vmw_dma_select_mode \- Determine how DMA mappings should be set up for this system.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" vmw_dma_select_mode
.BI "(struct vmw_private *dev_priv "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev_priv" 12
Pointer to a struct vmw_private
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This functions tries to determine what actions need to be taken by the
driver to make system pages visible to the device.
If this function decides that DMA is not possible, it returns -EINVAL.
The driver may then try to disable features of the device that require
DMA.
